call matchadd("search", "One of the bonuses of intermittent fasting is that it triggers the production of the human growth hormone, which naturally depletes with age (6). The human growth hormone (HgH) is produced during sleep and has amazing benefits for the body, including: Maintains, builds, and repairs healthy tissues in the brain and other organs Burns fat Boosts metabolism Builds muscle mass Slows aging process Improves quality and appearance of skin Speeds up healing and muscle repair")
